HEADWORD: Reverential
<hw>Rev`er*en"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧v⟦eacute⟧renciel</ets>. See <er>Reverence</er>.]</ety>
<def>Proceeding from, or expressing, reverence; having a reverent
quality; reverent; <as>as, <ex>reverential</ex> fear or awe</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>reverential</xex> esteem of things sacred.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

